snippet.textDisplay:
Have to admit that all Ali Hamza songs are quite unique. Loved the interplay between these two beautiful voices, perfect for a complementary duet like this one. The music arrangement is simple with the occasional rhythmic beauty by the drummer (00:56) and the flute pieces weaved in well.

I had liked Nirmay Roy a lot in her debut last season in 'Ala Baali' and I feel her vocals lend the simplicity that the song needs. The lyrics are playful and thoughtful at the same time. I like the conclusion where the pace of the song quickens, and ends with Ali Hamza repeating the mukhda. Good old technique to end songs :')
